                            <comment id="14736463" author="blambov" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2015 08:42:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Pushed &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/blambov/cassandra/tree/10219-2.1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;2.1&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/blambov/cassandra/tree/10219-3.0&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;3.0&lt;/a&gt; branches with fix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix replaces the &lt;tt&gt;skipPromoted&lt;/tt&gt; with &lt;tt&gt;skip&lt;/tt&gt; and adds a test of recovering the rest of the cache after losing an sstable. It is very rare that this could cause problems of any kind (truncation or drop are fine as the whole of the cache for that CF is invalid in that case), and since the potential problem is some missing cache entries I think we were right to not even log it at a significant level. Feel free to change the &quot;harmless error&quot; log level in &lt;tt&gt;AutoSavingCache&lt;/tt&gt; when committing if you disagree.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That exception wasn&apos;t even firing with the old code as the wrong skip causes the next read to see a very high length, which in turn causes the rest of the file to be skipped without raising an exception as &lt;tt&gt;FileInputStream&lt;/tt&gt; happily reports skipping over more than the length of the file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Both patches include warning clean-up; in the 3.0 version I&apos;ve taken the liberty to remove the generic type parameter of &lt;tt&gt;RowIndexEntry&lt;/tt&gt;, which wasn&apos;t used in any way but caused quite a few unnecessary raw type warnings.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14948976" author="snazy" created="Thu, 8 Oct 2015 16:52:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just a question: is this still an issue after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10359&quot; title=&quot;Saved caches use ambigous keyspace and CF name to identify tables&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-10359&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-10359&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14950101" author="blambov" created="Fri, 9 Oct 2015 09:00:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10155&quot; title=&quot;2i key cache load fails&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-10155&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-10155&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; does include the fix, so the only value of this is the added test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should I rebase to bring the test into the code, or do we close the ticket?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14950127" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 9 Oct 2015 09:32:07 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Should I rebase to bring the test into the code&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is the test testing something that isn&apos;t covered otherwise? That is, did &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10155&quot; title=&quot;2i key cache load fails&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-10155&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-10155&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added an equivalent test? If that test is still of value, then I&apos;ll just ninja-commit it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;the generic type parameter of RowIndexEntry, which wasn&apos;t used in any way&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fyi, I believe the reason for that parameter is &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3067&quot; title=&quot;Simple SSTable Pluggability&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-3067&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-3067&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Now, I&apos;m not really sure that pluggability still works in 3.0 and I have my doubt about trying to maintain such pluggability without making any concrete use of it, but let&apos;s not have this debate on this ticket &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14950176" author="blambov" created="Fri, 9 Oct 2015 10:29:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am not seeing an equivalent test, there is a DROP TABLE version which will go through the relevant code path but not fail with the bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14950209" author="snazy" created="Fri, 9 Oct 2015 11:02:08 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;If that test is still of value, then I&apos;ll just ninja-commit it.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also +1 on removing the generic part of RowIndexEntry as it buys us nothing. (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10320&quot; title=&quot;Build off-heap key-cache compatible API&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-10320&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-10320&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; would also remove the generics part.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14950341" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 9 Oct 2015 13:00:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Alright, committed the test, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
